Slaw: In a large bowl, whisk together vinegar, tamari, chili-garlic sauce and oil. Add cabbage, quinoa, carrot and green onions, gently tossing to combine. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Pork: In a medium bowl, whisk together sugar, ginger, tamari, apple juice, chili-garlic sauce and oil. Add pork and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 15 minutes. Remove half the pork slices from marinade, shaking off excess. In a large, deep skillet, cook pork over medium high heat, stirring, for 2 to 4 minutes or until browned on all sides and just a hint of pink remains inside: Transfer to a plate. Repeat with the remaining pork, discarding marinade. Return all pork to skillet and cook, stirring, until heated through. Serve pork with slaw: Garnish with sesame seeds, if desired.